This is a late night foodie’s paradise.  Has a full service food menu until serving until 3am??? What?!?  I had the Kalbi Beef Steak appetizer.  It came with the perfect amount of kalbi beef steak, coconut rice, and kimchee!  It can get busy late night, but I’ve always been able to get a table and get some great food.  Ho yea there is a bar with TVs at the end of the main room. It really is one of my favorite places to go to in Waikiki.  Awesome!

Best place for a late meal after 12am. After working all day what is great about this place is that have a solid menu. From quick appetizers to full entrees, you cannot go wrong here. There is plenty of space to sit as well as a bar in the far back of restaurant. Prices are fair but the staff is super friendly which has you coming back time after time. Must try. This is for sure a hidden gem in Waikiki.

I use to go here all the time after work! Slowly they changed certain things. But after this last visit I'm very disappointed. It would seem that the entire Menu was taken out and replaced with one that's not even a quarter of the size!  Not only that but the prices of everything besides drinks almost doubled!  The new menu Items look like they are trying to be fancy and not causal. But it's the large causal menu that tasted good that brought myself and others in.  There was no better place to get some late-night food in Waikiki. But unfortunately they have lost the magic with this weird change.  Looks like i won't be coming back anymore unless they either add to the menu or bring back alot of items.  Myself and others that were long time customers won't be choosing this spot as our latenight food and drink destination.  What a shame...

The best part about this place is that it doesn't get crowded. The prices of the food and drinks are reasonable too. They do have happy hour, but it doesn't make much of a difference since the original prices are pretty good already. So you can pretty much go whenever. If you're in Waikiki and you want a place to enjoy some grub and drinks with a few friends without so much of crowd and noise, I recommend going here.
